#use wml::debian::ddp title="DDP Administrators' Manuals"

<h2><a name="install">Debian Installation Manual</a></h2>

<blockquote>
  Installation instructions for the Debian GNU/Linux distribution.
<p>
<table><tr>
  <td><strong>Authors:</strong></td>
  <td>Bruce Perens, Sven Rudolph, Igor Grobman, James Treacy, Adam Di Carlo
  </td>
 </tr><tr>
  <td><strong>Maintainer:</strong></td>
  <td>Adam Di Carlo</td>
 </tr><tr>
  <td valign="top"><strong>Status:</strong></td>
  <td>Active work being done for Debian releases (2.1, 2.2). Need help with
  non-x86 installation and non-English language versions; please volunteer,
  this is very important to Debian. Contact debian-boot@lists.debian.org for
  more information.</td>
 </tr><tr>
  <td valign="top"><strong>Availability:</strong></td>
  <td>Debian package <strong>boot-floppies</strong> and
  <tt>ftp://ftp.debian.org/pub/dists/{stable,unstable}/disks-*/current/install.html</tt>

  <p><a href="http://ftp.debian.org/debian/dists/stable/main/disks-i386/current/install.en.html">
  Released version for stable (2.1), i386 arch</a>,<br>
  <a href="http://ftp.debian.org/debian/dists/frozen/main/disks-i386/current/doc/install.en.html">
  Version being prepared for the next stable (frozen, 2.2), i386 arch</a>,<br>
  CVS sources working copy: set <code>CVSROOT</code> to
    <kbd>:ext:<var>userid</var>@cvs.debian.org:/cvs/debian-boot</kbd>,
  and check out the <kbd>boot-floppies/documentation</kbd> module.
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>
</blockquote>

